Atlas version 3.7 is a model-finder for geometric theories.


# Build

  * Run make from terminal.

# Run

  atlas

  -i FILE     --input=FILE, --file=FILE	Input theory file
  -b #	      --bound=#	    		Bound for bounded model-finding
  -d          --debug	    		Show debug information
  -s bfs/dfs  --schedule=bfs/dfs	Use schedule type (depth-first-search,
     /rr      /rr			breadth-first-search, or round-robing)
  -t 	      --batch			Enable batch processing
  -n 	      --incremental		Enable incremental view maintenance
  -1 	      --one			Display only one models (by default,
     	      				Atlas builds all models)
  	      --process-unit=#		Process unit for round-robin scheduling
	      --tptp-path		Path to TPTP library
  -f geo/fof  --formula-type=geo/fof    The input type (geometric formula, TPTP
     /cnf     /cnf			FOF or TPTP CNF)
              --skolem-depth=#          Depth of skolem term for reusing elements
	      				(-1 for pure minimal models and 0 for 
					random collapse)
  -h          --help			Show help
  -v          --version			Print version


# Remarks

  * --incremental is expected to improve the efficiency of the chase for non-equational
  theories. It significantly hurts the efficiency as the number of equations in the
  theory increases.
  * --batch is buggy.